# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# env file
.env

# Editor/IDE
# .idea/
# .vscode/

# --- bankferry: project-specific (merged in; the stock template above is unchanged) ---

# Editor/agent local state. The stock Editor/IDE lines above are commented out;
# activate the ones this project actually produces.
.idea/
.claude/

# Built binary. The stock *.exe covers Windows; this catches the extensionless
# Unix/macOS build (go build -o bankferry).
/bankferry

# Local SQLite database and its WAL/SHM sidecars. The path is set in .env; this
# also matches casing variants like bankFerry.db.
/[Bb]ank[Ff]erry.db*

# Encrypted credential backups and exports — local only, never published.
*.encryptedBackup
*.tapb

# Working migration checklist — never publish (removed once the move is done).
MIGRATION.md
